Kodansha recognizes the importance of your personal information, and hereby prescribes and applies this Privacy Policy for the proper collection, use and protection, as well as the
              safety control, of your personal information.
1) Definition of personal information
In this Privacy Policy, the term “personal information” means information about a living individual which corresponds to one of the following.
Information which can identify a specific individual by name, date of birth or other description contained in such information {meaning any matter (excluding an individual
                identification code) stated, recorded or otherwise expressed using voice, motion or other methods in a document, drawing or electromagnetic record (meaning a record which is created in
                electronic form, magnetic form, or any other form that cannot be perceived by the human senses) (including such information as will allow easy reference to other information and will
                thereby enable the identification of the specific individual).
Information which contains an individual identification code.
2) Management of personal information
Kodansha will properly manage your personal information by prescribing application guidelines related to the protection of personal information, and appointing a personal information
              administrator.
3) Collection of personal information
When collecting your personal information, Kodansha will designate the purpose of utilization of your personal information and notify you of such purpose of utilization in advance, and
              collect and use your personal information by adequate means within the scope required for attaining such purpose of utilization. Furthermore, unless otherwise prescribed in the “Act on
              the Protection of Personal Information” (Act No. 57 of 2003; hereinafter referred to as the “Personal Information Protection Act”), Kodansha will not use the collected personal
              information for any purpose other than for the purpose of utilization without obtaining your prior consent, and will endeavor to promptly erase your personal information after attaining
              the purpose of utilization.
4) Purpose of utilization of personal information
Kodansha may ask you to provide your personal information for the following purpose of utilization. When collecting and using your personal information for any purpose other than the
              following purpose of utilization, Kodansha will notify you of such purpose of utilization pursuant to the preceding paragraph.
(1) To provide services for registered members
(2) To send products and prizes that you ordered or applied for
(3) To conduct research and analysis through questionnaires in order to improve our existing services, develop our new services, and maximize customer satisfaction, etc.
(4) To notify results to persons who cooperated with our questionnaires or events
(5) To provide information through direct mails or emails, etc.
(6) To improve or upgrade services or develop new services of Kodansha’s website or various online services (hereinafter collectively referred to as the “Official Site, etc.”)
(7) To analyze your interests and preferences using information collected by Kodansha and its affiliated companies, etc. in order to improve Kodansha’s services, such as contacting,
                informing and guiding you about products and events that better meet your needs
(8) To execute business operations related to the purposes of (1) to (7) above
In the Official Site, etc., you can choose whether or not to provide your personal information to
                Kodansha based on your own judgment; provided, however, that, if you decide not to provide your personal information to Kodansha, you may not be able to use the services offered in the
                Official Site, etc.
5) Provision of personal information to a third party
Kodansha will not provide your personal information to any third party unless we obtain your approval, such provision is based on the Personal Information Protection Act or other laws
              and regulations, or any of the following cases apply.
Cases in which the provision of personal data is necessary for the protection of the life, body, or property of an individual and in which it is difficult to obtain your consent
Cases in which the provision of personal data is especially necessary for improving public health or promoting the sound growth of children and in which it is difficult to obtain your
                consent
Cases in which the provision of personal data is necessary for cooperating with a state organ, a local government, or an individual or a business operator entrusted by one in executing
                the affairs prescribed by laws and regulations and in which obtaining your consent are likely to impede the execution of the affairs
Cases of confirming the validity of bank accounts or credit cards of users with financial institutions or credit card companies in connection with the credit card payment of fee-based
                services or ordered products
Kodansha will not provide your personal information to a third party located overseas unless we obtain your approval or such provision is allowed under the Personal Information
                Protection Act.
When you purchase or use Kodansha products, respond to surveys, enter campaigns or otherwise use Kodansha’s services, Kodansha may provide personal information in its possession to
Content Data Marketing Inc.,
an affiliate of Kodansha, to the extent necessary for Kodansha and Content Data Marketing Inc. to
                provide improved services. For information on the purposes of use of your personal data by Content Data Marketing Inc., please refer to the privacy policy of Content Data Marketing
                Inc.
6) Records, etc. upon provision and reception of personal information
When Kodansha is to provide personal information to a third party (excluding a state organ, local government, incorporated administrative agency, etc. and local independent
              administrative institution; hereinafter the same in this paragraph) or receive personal information from a third party, we will create records concerning necessary matters pursuant to
              the Personal Information Protection Act, and store such records during the period prescribed in the Rules of the Personal Information Protection Commission.
7) Security Control Measures for protection of personal information
Kodansha will take necessary and proper systematic, human, physical and technical security control measures for the prevention of leakage, loss or damage of personal information. For
              more information on security control measures, please contact us via the method set forth below in “11) Contact us”.
8) Entrustment to a third party
When Kodansha is to entrust the handling of personal information to a third party, we will appoint a proper trustee, exchange a contract related to the protection of personal information
              with the trustee, and exercise necessary and appropriate supervision over the trustee.
9) Disclosure, correction suspension or deletion of use of personal information
When Kodansha receives your request for the disclosure (including the disclosure of records on third-party provision), correction, suspension, deletion or cessation of third-party
              provision, we will take measures properly and promptly pursuant to the Personal Information Protection Act. For details, please read “
Procedures for Personal Information Held by Kodansha
”.
10) Amendment of this Privacy Policy
Kodansha may amend this Privacy Policy without prior notice due to changes in social situations, advancement of technologies or revision of the Personal Information Protection Act.
Please note that this Privacy Policy shall not apply to cases of news coverage, etc.
11) Contact us
If you have any inquiries regarding the subject matter of this page, please use this
Contact Form
.
Use of access data in Kodansha’s official website and various online services
The website and various online services operated by Kodansha (hereinafter collectively referred to as the “Official Site, etc.”) will handle the access data of users in the Official
              Site, etc. with utmost attention as described below. Furthermore, Kodansha will handle the collected personal information according to the foregoing Privacy Policy.
1) Definition of access data
The term “access data” means, among all information handled by Kodansha which can directly or indirectly identify a user as an individual (hereinafter referred to as the “Personal
              Data”), date/time and frequency of access, IP address, terminal, browser (internet browser) and type/version of OS used, screen size, Cookie information, referrer information, GPS
              position information, browsing history of pages and articles, time spent on each page, and trail of the cursor (mouse).
2) Purpose of utilization of access data
Kodansha may automatically acquire the access data of users of the Official Site, etc. for the following purpose of utilization.
(1) To provide services for registered members
(2) To notify results to persons who cooperated with our questionnaires or events
(3) To provide information through direct mails or emails, etc.
(4) To distribute ads (targeted ads) that meet the needs of users, confirm the status of distribution, and measure the effect of such ads
(5) To improve or upgrade services or develop new services of the Official Site, etc.
(6) To execute business operations related to the purposes of (1) to (5) above
3) Use of Cookies
A Cookie is information that is exchanged between the web server and your browser when you browse a webpage, and is recorded at a prescribed location of the browser when the setting on
              your PC or mobile terminal accepts the use of Cookies; provided, however, that the recorded information does not include any information which can identify a specific individual, such as
              the username or email address. In the Official Site, etc., you can use the information remaining in the Cookies and change the display to your liking. You can also change the setting of
              the browser to refuse the use of Cookies or to display a warning when Cookies are being used; provided, however, that, in such a case, please note that you may not be able to use certain
              services or functions depending on the site.
4) Opt-out (disabling) of Cookies
You can change the setting of your browser to receive a notice when Cookies are being used or refuse the use of Cookies. If you refuse the use of Cookies, articles and ads that meet your
              needs may no longer be displayed or distributed, or the same ad may be repeatedly distributed.
5) Web beacon
The Official Site, etc. and certain HTML email magazines may acquire the access status of the Official Site, etc. by combining a technology known as “web beacon” with Cookies.
6) Ad distribution by a third-party service provider
In certain sites and services among the Official Site, etc., Kodansha is entrusting the ad distribution to a third-party service provider for the ads to be displayed on such sites and
              online services, and Kodansha’s ads to be displayed on various external websites and online services. For the ad distribution described above, the ad provider as our trustee may also
              acquire and use your Cookies. In such a case, the acquired Cookies will be stored and managed on the server of the ad provider, and not on our web server.
7) Targeting ads distributed by ad provider
On the Official Site, etc., the targeting ads by the following ad providers are being distributed. For the details regarding the targeting ads of the respective ad providers and the
              method of invalidating ad distribution, please visit the website of the respective ad providers.
AdCorsa (Glossom, Inc.)
