3. Purpose of Use and Legal Basis
Kodansha will process the personal data for the following purposes of use. Please note that the legal basis for processing personal data may vary depending on the jurisdiction. When a
              basis specified below does not apply in your jurisdiction, we will process your personal data based on an alternative basis permitted under the applicable laws and regulations, such as
              obtaining your consent.
(1)For Kodansha’s legitimate interests in which personal data is strictly required to carry out its business activities (including the following purposes of use):
(a) To statistically process personal data, and use or provide the processed data;
(b) To conduct research and analysis through questionnaires in order to improve our existing services, develop our new services, and maximize customer satisfaction, etc.;
(c) To notify persons who filled out questionnaires or participated in events of the thereof;
(d) To improve or upgrade services or develop new services for Kodansha’s website or for various other online services;
(e) To respond to your enquiries regarding secondary use of our publications, etc.;
(f) To contact you as necessary for our business; and
(g) To manage Kodansha’s projects and other activities to which you have applied.
(2)To comply with obligations under an agreement or to perform the procedures relating to an agreement (including the following purposes of use):
(a) To provide services to registered members and enable them efficient use thereof;
(b) To process and administer their personal account and register for those services;
(c) To send products and prizes that you ordered or applied for; and
(d) To process your payments.
(3)To process personal data in the event you give consent (including the following purposes of use):
(a) To distribute targeted ads based on your use of Kodansha’s services and/or on third-party sites and applications, confirm the status of distribution, and measure the effect of
                    such ads; and
(b) To provide information regarding Kodansha’s services and other products, etc. through direct mail or email, etc.
(4)For purposes set forth in the laws and regulations (including the following purposes of use):
(a) For use in the event there is a need to maintain or acquire personal data to fulfill a legal obligation borne by Kodansha; and
(b) When responding to requests of the government or investigative agencies.
We do not make decisions that may affect you legally or in a similarly significant manner based solely on automated processes.
4. Recipients of Personal Data
Kodansha will process and provide your personal data to the following businesses:
advertising networks and data analytics providers;
shipping and payment companies;
customer management service providers;
IT infrastructure service providers
web hosting vendors;
security service providers; and
cloud service providers
Kodansha will subcontract the processing of personal data after executing memorandums of understanding concerning the entrustment of the processing of personal data with service
              providers.
Kodansha will also disclose your country of residence along with your comment on K Manga when you post a comment.
5. Transfer to Third Country
Kodansha may transfer your personal data to countries outside your country, including Japan, to provide its services. Such countries may have a lower level of data protection than your
              country. When providing personal data to third parties outside your country, Kodansha takes the necessary measures therefor, such as obtaining consent and concluding data transfer
              agreements, etc., in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.
In the event that the GDPR applies to the processing of your personal data, Kodansha will only transfer personal data to third countries where an adequacy decision has not been given if
              proper protective measures such, as of the standard data protection provisions set forth in Article 46(2) of the GDPR, are in place.
To obtain a copy of a document used for the protection of your personal data or to obtain detailed information, please send a letter to Kodansha (2-21-21 Otowa, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo ) or an
              email to privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp.
6. Retention Period
Kodansha will retain your personal data for the period of time required to achieve the purpose of use set forth in this Global Policy. The decision on the retention period of personal
              data is based on (i) whether or not you continue to use Kodansha’s services, (ii) whether or not there are legal obligations that Kodansha must comply with, and (iii) whether or not
              there is a need to perform an agreement to which you are a party.
7. Your Rights
You may have specific rights as a data subject under applicable laws and regulations, such as (i) the right to request a copy of the personal data, (ii) the right to request revisions,
              (iii) the right to request deletions, (iv) the right to limit or stop the processing of personal data, and (v) the right to have the personal data provided to Kodansha for an agreement
              or under consent be structured and receive it in a form that is machine-readable (right of data portability). Regardless of your request for deletion, Kodansha will continue to retain
              the necessary information for measures against re-rolling, as permitted by law.
In addition thereto, where the GDPR applies, you also have (vi) the right to object to the processing of personal data, under certain conditions. Please refer to “9. Right to File
              Objection” below for details.
These rights may be restricted, for example, if a third party’s personal data is disclosed by complying with your request, if the rights of someone other than you (including Kodansha’s
              rights) will be infringed, or if retention is required or deletion of information of which its retention has exigent legitimate interests is required by the laws and regulations.
To exercise any of these rights, please send a letter to Kodansha (2-21-21 Otowa, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo) or an email to
privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp
. Note we may require proof of your identity and full details of your request or complaint before we can
              process them. We will respond to your request or complaint within the timeframe determined by the applicable laws and regulations. It will not always be possible to resolve a complaint
              to everyone’s satisfaction. If you are not satisfied with Kodansha’s response to your request or complaint, you have the right to contact the supervising authorities to lodge a
              complaint. For details, see “11. Right to File Complaint with Supervising Authorities” below.
8. Right to File Objection
You may have the right to file an objection to the processing of personal data.
Where the GDPR applies, you can object to the processing based on legitimate interests. The processing of personal data subject to such objection includes profiling (which means
              analyzing and predicting your actions from your information; the same applies hereafter). If your personal data is processed for the purpose of direct marketing, you have the absolute
              right to refuse direct marketing and to refuse the profiling conducted for such purpose.
To exercise any of these rights, please send a letter to Kodansha (2-21-21 Otowa, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo) or an email to
privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp
.
9. Right to Withdraw Consent
If Kodansha is processing personal data under your consent, you always have the right to withdraw such consent. This withdrawal will not have effect on the legality of any processing
              that was conducted under the consent granted before then.
To exercise this right, please send a letter to Kodansha (2-21-21 Otowa, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo) or an email to privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp.
10. Personal Data Required to be Provided
The personal data that is required to be provided will be indicated on the form that you fill out. If the provision of personal data is required, Kodansha will not be able to provide its
              services to you unless proper information is provided.
11. Right to File Complaint with Supervising Authorities
You have the right to file a complaint with supervising authorities. Supervising authorities with which the complaint can be filed include the supervising authorities of countries where
              your place of residence or workplace is located or where the place the petition of the violation is initiated is located.
12. Changes to this Global Policy
Kodansha will update this Global Policy from time to time in its sole discretion. We encourage you to look for updates and changes to this Global Policy periodically. If we make a
              material change to this Global Policy, we will endeavor to notify you on our services pages, by email, and/or by other legally permissible communication as required by applicable laws.
13. Questions
To learn more about our privacy policies, standards, or codes, etc., please send a letter to Kodansha (2-21-21 Otowa, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo) or an email to
privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp
.
