                companies; and
All categories of personal information to service providers, including cloud service providers.
4. Sale or Sharing of Personal Information
Kodansha has shared your personal information collected from you with third parties for purposes of cross-context behavioral advertising in the preceding twelve (12) months. Therefore,
              you have the “right to opt-out” of such sharing of your personal information under the CCPA. For more information about the right to opt-out, please see 5(4) below.
Kodansha has not sold any personal information collected from you in the preceding twelve (12) months.
5. Your Rights under the CCPA
The CCPA provides specific rights regarding personal information to consumers who are residents of California. This Section describes your rights and explains how to exercise those
              rights under the CCPA.
(1) Right to Access Specific Information
You have the right to request that we disclose certain information to you about our collection, sharing, disclosure, and use of your personal information. Once Kodansha receives and
              confirms your verifiable consumer request, Kodansha will disclose any or all of the following information to you:
The categories of the personal information that Kodansha has collected about you;
The categories of the sources from which the personal information is collected;
Kodansha’s business or commercial purpose for collecting, selling, or sharing such personal information;
The categories of third parties to which Kodansha disclosed such personal information; and
The specific pieces of personal information Kodansha has collected about you.
(2) Right to Request Deletion
You have the right to request that Kodansha delete any of your personal information that Kodansha has collected from you and retained, subject to certain exceptions. Upon receiving and
              confirming your verifiable consumer request, Kodansha will delete, and notify our service providers or contractors and third parties to whom Kodansha has sold or shared such personal
              information to delete, your personal information from Kodansha’s records, unless an exception applies.
Kodansha may deny your request for deletion if retaining the information is necessary for Kodansha or its service providers or contractors to:
Complete the transaction for which Kodansha collected the personal information, provide a good or service that you requested, take actions reasonably anticipated within the context of
                Kodansha’s ongoing business relationship with you, or otherwise perform Kodansha’s contract with you;
Help to ensure security and integrity to the extent the use of your personal information is reasonably necessary and proportionate for those purposes;
Debug products to identify and repair errors that impair existing intended functionality;
Exercise free speech, ensure the rights of other consumers to exercise their free speech rights, or exercise other rights provided by law;
Comply with the California Electronic Communications Privacy Act (Cal. Penal Code § 1546 et. seq.);
Engage in public or peer reviewed scientific, historical, or statistical research that conforms or adheres to all other applicable ethics and privacy laws, when our deletion of the
                information is likely to render impossible or seriously impair the ability to complete such research, if you have provided informed consent;
Enable solely internal uses that are reasonably aligned with your expectations based on your relationship with Kodansha and compatible with the context in which you provided the
                information; or
Comply with legal obligations.
(3) Right to Request Correction of Inaccurate Personal Information
You have the right to request that Kodansha correct any inaccuracies regarding your personal information that Kodansha has collected from you and retained, subject to certain exceptions.
              Upon receiving and confirming your verifiable request, Kodansha will correct, and notify our service providers or contractors and third parties to whom Kodansha has sold or shared such
              personal information to correct, your inaccurate personal information.
Kodansha may deny your request for correction if Kodansha determines that the contested personal information is more likely than not accurate based on the totality of the circumstances.
(4) Right to Opt-Out of Sale or Sharing
You have the right to opt-out of having your personal information shared for purposes of cross-context behavioral advertising. To exercise your right to opt-out of your personal
              information, you (or your authorized representative) may submit a request through one of the following methods:
For K MANGA users
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
Cookie settings
For Licensing Website users
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
The manner set forth in Section 8 (Contact Us)
(5) Right to Limit the Use and Disclosure of Sensitive Personal Information
Kodansha has not used or disclosed and will not use or disclose sensitive personal information collected from you for any purpose other than the following:
Perform the services or provide the goods reasonably expected by an average consumer who requests such goods or services;
Help to ensure security and integrity to the extent the use of your personal information is reasonably necessary and proportionate for those purposes;
Short-term, transient use (except those involving profiling or changes to the future consumer experience);
Perform services on behalf of us; and
Undertake activities to verify or maintain the quality or safety of a service or device that is owned, manufactured, manufactured for, or controlled by us.
(6) Right to Non-Discrimination
Kodansha will not discriminate against California residents for exercising any of your rights under the CCPA. Unless permitted by the CCPA, Kodansha will not:
Deny you goods or services;
Charge you different prices or rates for goods or services, including through granting discounts or other benefits or imposing penalties;
Provide you with a different level or quality of goods or services;
Suggest that you may receive a different price or rate for goods or services or a different level or quality of goods or services; or
Retaliate against an employee, applicant for employment, or independent contractor.
(7) Exercising Rights under the CCPA
To exercise your rights under the CCPA to access, delete, or correct your personal information as described above, please submit a verifiable consumer request to us by contacting us in
              the manner set forth in Section 8 (Contact Us).
Only you, or a person registered with the California Secretary of State that you authorize to act on your behalf, or a person who has power of attorney or is acting as a your conservator
              may make a verifiable consumer request related to your personal information. You may also make a verifiable consumer request on behalf of your minor child.
The verifiable consumer request must:
Provide sufficient information that allows Kodansha to reasonably verify that you are the person whose personal information Kodansha has collected or an authorized representative
                thereof (e.g. contact Enquiry ID, email address, etc.); and
Describe your request with sufficient detail that allows Kodansha to properly understand, evaluate, and respond thereto.
6. Retention Period
Kodansha will retain your personal information for the period of time required to achieve the purpose of use set forth in this California Policy.
The retention period of personal data relies on (i) whether you continue to use Kodansha’s services, (ii) whether there are legal obligations that Kodansha must comply with, and (iii)
              whether there is a need to perform an agreement to which you are a party.
7. Processing of Personal Information of Children
Our services are not directed to and we do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a
              child under the age of 13 without the consent of the child’s parent or guardian, we will delete it. We encourage parents with concerns to contact us in the manner set forth in Section 8
              (Contact Us).
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or comments about this California Policy or the ways in which Kodansha collects and uses your personal information or if you wish to exercise your rights under
              the CCPA, please do not hesitate to contact
privacycenter@kodansha.co.jp
.
